<TITLE> BNP calls half-day strike after DCC ward chief shot dead </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 10 (bdnews24.com)  BNP has called a half-day strike in Dhaka's Ward 70 on Thursday, protesting the death of Dhaka city ward commissioner Haji Ahmed Hossain who was gunned down in Bangshal, Old Dhaka, on Tuesday night. Other programmes include doa mahfil at the party's Naya Paltan headquarters on Friday and a protest rally in Muktangan at 3pm on Saturday. Three namaz-e-janazas will be held for Hossain on Wednesday, the first one will be held at Nagar Bhaban at 12:30pm, the second one in the party's headquarters after Zohr prayers and the last at the local mosque of Ward 70. The BNP backed ward commissioner was a leader of Jubo Dal, which will bring out a protest and mourning procession on Thursday. b
